cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper discusses a scheme for exceptional access to devices that balances privacy and law enforcement desires. It involves encryption and security measures, which are typical topics in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of networks and delegates, which could fall under the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a concrete construction and aims to spur discussion on ethical exceptional access schemes, which could be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of resources and costs, which could relate to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
